+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012ew9h9JGfV5GQXBpzACzkY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01GBvyswQdX5hUzqpTMJpczu","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"gemini -p \"You are implementing an event-driven e-commerce backend in TypeScript. The project uses vitest for tests, TypeScript strict mode, ESM modules (type: module in package.json, module: Node16 in tsconfig).\n\nIMPORTANT FILES (read-only, do NOT modify):\n- src/bus.ts -- EventBus class with on/off/emit/getLog/clear methods. emit is async.\n- src/types.ts -- All interfaces, enums (OrderStatus, PaymentStatus), event payload types, Events constants.\n\nYou need to implement 8 services, each in its own file:\n1. src/catalog/index.ts - createCatalogService(bus: EventBus): CatalogService\n2. src/inventory/index.ts - createInventoryService(bus: EventBus): InventoryService\n3. src/cart/index.ts - createCartService(bus: EventBus): CartService\n4. src/pricing/index.ts - createPricingService(bus: EventBus): PricingService\n5. src/orders/index.ts - createOrderService(bus: EventBus): OrderService\n6. src/payment/index.ts - createPaymentService(bus: EventBus, options?): PaymentService\n7. src/notifications/index.ts - createNotificationService(bus: EventBus): NotificationService\n8. src/analytics/index.ts - createAnalyticsService(bus: EventBus): AnalyticsService\n\nAlso create src/index.ts that re-exports all 8 factory functions.\n\nKey requirements:\n- Services must NOT import from each other. All communication via EventBus events.\n- Use uuid package (import { v4 as uuidv4 } from 'uuid') for generating IDs.\n- Catalog: CRUD for products. Emit Events.PRODUCT_CREATED with ProductCreatedEvent payload on create.\n- Inventory: track stock per product. reserve() returns false if insufficient stock. setLowStockThreshold + emit Events.LOW_STOCK_ALERT (LowStockAlertEvent) when stock drops below threshold. Emit Events.INVENTORY_UPDATED on changes.\n- Cart: manage carts per user. addItem consolidates quantities for same productId. Emit Events.CART_UPDATED on changes.\n- Pricing: calculateTotal with items array, optional discountCode. Tax rate 10%. discount reduces subtotal before tax. Listen for Events.PRODUCT_CREATED to cache prices. getPrice returns cached price. addDiscountCode registers percentage discount.\n- Orders: createOrder returns orderId. Orders start PENDING. updateStatus changes status, emits Events.ORDER_STATUS_CHANGED with OrderStatusChangedEvent (includes previousStatus). Emit Events.ORDER_CREATED on creation.\n- Payment: processPayment is async. Options param can have simulateFailure, simulateTimeout (booleans). Default: success. Generate transactionId. Emit Events.PAYMENT_PROCESSED. refund returns true for successful transactions.\n- Notifications: subscribe(userId). Listen for Events.ORDER_STATUS_CHANGED and Events.PAYMENT_PROCESSED. Record notifications with type/message/timestamp. Need to track orderId->userId mapping by listening to Events.ORDER_CREATED.\n- Analytics: listen to ALL events (PRODUCT_CREATED, CART_UPDATED, ORDER_CREATED, PAYMENT_PROCESSED). Count events by type. Track revenue from successful payments. Conversion rate = orders / unique carts. getTopProducts: track product quantities from ORDER_CREATED events (need to listen for cart data).\n\nAfter implementing all services, write comprehensive tests in src/__tests__/services.test.ts covering all services.\n\nCRITICAL: \n- This is ESM. Use .js extensions in relative imports (e.g., import { EventBus } from '../bus.js').\n- The EventBus.emit is async, so any place calling bus.emit must await it.\n- Make sure all types match the interfaces in types.ts exactly.\n- For analytics getTopProducts: listen to ORDER_CREATED events, then look at cart data from CART_UPDATED events to know which products were ordered.\n- For analytics conversion rate: track unique cart IDs from CART_UPDATED events and order count from ORDER_CREATED events.\n\nRead src/types.ts and src/bus.ts first. Then implement all services. Then write tests. Run 'npm test', 'npm run build', 'npm run lint'. Fix any failures. Don't stop until all pass.\" -y 2>&1 | tail -200","description":"Dispatch full implementation to Gemini","timeout":600000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":208,"cache_read_input_tokens":21792,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":208},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"29c98f28-5ac4-4584-b05b-fec353cff98f","uuid":"656f9a34-0cf1-4f49-adef-792cd8875dd5"}
